19/12/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Fatos Nano said Thursday (18 December) that co-operation with the Geneva Centre for Security Policy (GCSP) would provide invaluable help to Albania's Euro-Atlantic integration efforts. He met with the GCSP Director Gerard Stoudmann in Tirana. Stoudmann in turn praised Albania's role in securing peace and stability in the region and said the GCSP followed developments in Albania with interest. Nano and Stoudmann agreed on the importance of implementing joint training projects in defence and domestic security. (ATA - 18/12/03)
